# BMO Stack Environment Variables
# Copy this file to .env and fill in the values

# OpenClaw / NVIDIA API Configuration (required for AI model)
NVIDIA_API_KEY=your_nvidia_api_key_here

# Note: Telegram Bot Token is NOT required here because:
#   - The OpenClaw gateway (which handles Telegram) runs on the host machine
#   - Configure Telegram via: openclaw configure --section channels
#   - See: https://docs.openclaw.ai/guides/telegram-bot

# Optional: If you choose to run auxiliary services in Docker (e.g., PostgreSQL)
#   - Uncomment and configure the service in compose.yaml
#   - Add any required environment variables for those services here
#   - Example for PostgreSQL:
#   POSTGRES_USER=bmouser
#   POSTGRES_PASSWORD=postgres
#   POSTGRES_DB=bmo